  "texts": [
    "Based on the number of perspectives used for feature extraction, it can be divided into single-view and multi-view methods.",
    "Single-view human reconstruction is less restricted by the environment than multi-view approaches, and the corresponding accuracy of the reconstructed 3D model is often lower.",
    "In a similar way to 3D face reconstruction, 3D human body reconstruction also requires strong prior models as support.",
    "Hence, general body modeling methods such as SCAPE (Anguelov et al. 2005) and SMPL (Loper et al. 2015) are widely used for 3D reconstruction.",
    "Statistical body shape models, as a powerful human prior, allow for convenient disentanglement of pose and shape."
  ],
